node.text: Leandre Sanders, aka The @SkateGoat: "I want to share this with you all, the film about my life. Here is the trailer filmed by @van_alpert so excited to say we he is now done with the SkateGoat movie and ready to change the world by bringing families together with love. From the time I was 11 years old till now it documents 13 years of my life, my struggle, and the evolution of my skating. LOVE YOU ALL" 🎥 @van_alpert @allday #skateboardingisfun #berrics #skategoatmovie

node.text: Its @alexmidler’s 23rd birthday today! 🥳 With all that he’s done at The Berrics (and all around the world), it’s hard to believe that he’s only 23 years old. Here’s just a taste of some of the incredible clips he’s gotten within these walls. Make sure you go wish Alex a very special Happy Birthday and be on the lookout for his #BATB12 game premiering this weekend! Happy Birthday Midler!! 🎂🎁 #skateboardingisfun #berrics

node.text: @evon_martinez with the FAST FEET! 💥💨 See everyone? Evon caaan do a kickflip (even if the nerves made him miss one in BATB) 😆 #skateboardingisfun #berrics

@skatecitygame Tokyo level is now available in the Apple Arcade 📲🛹 Skateboarding is reaching a new cultural milestone this summer, and to celebrate the moment @skatecitygame will be releasing its biggest and best city to date, recreating the vibrant city streets of Tokyo itself in their game’s iconic style. Players will be able to skate through a diverse range of neighborhoods and famous skate spots to experience Tokyo’s unique identity. The level will blend the iconic, neon soaked city centers together with character rich backstreets, and beautiful parks. Tokyo will come complete with over 50 new challenges in Free Skate and Challenge mode for players to try and complete along with new leaderboards, deck designs, updated clothes to pick up in our skate shop, and new original songs that expand on our popular soundtrack. Skate City Tokyo lands exclusively on Apple Arcade on July 23rd 2021. 📲 #skatecitygame #skateboardingisfun #berrics

node.text: History is in the making! Skateboarding makes its Olympic debut this weekend!! The 2020 Tokyo Olympics Opening Ceremony was last night and the first time ever, the best skateboarders from around the world were part of the ceremony. With the Olympics underway, make sure to tune to NBC or their streaming service PeacockTV this Saturday & Sunday for Men's and Women's Street, respectfully, at 4:30pm PST for qualifications, and 8:30pm PST for the Street finals. More info to watch can be found at nbcolympics.com/skateboarding. Good luck to all the skateboarders making history and showing skateboarding to millions of people who have never seen it before. We can wait to watch it all go down. Tune in this weekend! #skateboardingisfun #berrics
